        <q>Page 16, line 14, leave out paragraph (f).</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-06366'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040524_GCR_85' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Baroness said: This is a simple amendment. It merely seeks to remove the power that paragraph (f) would give, empowering the Secretary of
        <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_416gc' title='Col. 416GC &mdash; HL Deb 24 May 2004 vol 661 c416GC' name='column_416gc' href='#column_416gc' rel='bookmark'>416GC</a>
